name: What a Hoot!
description:
I wish I new where the term "What a hoot" came from. I have no idea why it makes me think of the 70's and macrame owls sitting on driftwood. In any case, this little owl necklace has so much personality and charm, I'm willing to bet you'll hear the term a lot more when you wear it!

This necklace is made from a very pretty mossy green jade bead that is approx. 1 inch tall. Hanging at the top of the jade is a silver toned flower charm and who could forget the star of the show hanging from the bottom...the silver toned owl with green Swarovski crystal eyes. All of this hangs from a 16 1/2" silver toned chain.

name: Hooo's Your Daddy
description:
This little owl is quite the charmer. He's got a million pick up lines to try out on you. Of course the one he uses most is "Hooo's your daddy?" Yep...you know it works every time!

This necklace is made from a pretty green square glass bead (that looks a whole lot like a tiny jolly rancher) in between two small orange glass beads. From the top hangs a tiny silver toned flower and leaf charm. And of course from the bottom hangs Mr. Owl. This is a silver toned charm with green Swarovski crystal eyes. All of this hangs from an 18" silver toned chain.
